The shrine precincts include the {{ill|Fuji mound|ja|富士塚|qq=draft|qq=draft}} known as "Shimokamata no Fujizuka," which was constructed in 1916 by the {{ill|Fujikō|ja|富士講|qq=draft|qq=draft}} group, "Shimokamata Waribishi Hakkō-kō." The mound is registered as a tangible cultural asset of Edogawa City.<ref name="Historical Walk"/> {{sfn|江戸川区 下鎌田の富士塚}}.

== Cultural Properties ==
* '''Toyota Shrine Forest''' - Designated as a natural monument of Edogawa City on February 8, 1982.{{sfn|江戸川区 豊田神社の社叢}}
* '''Shimokamata Fujizuka''' - Registered as a tangible folk cultural property of Edogawa City on March 15, 1983.{{sfn|江戸川区 下鎌田の富士塚}}

